fullText: Tracie Bennett's uncanny impersonation of Judy Garland in her final, tragic phase is so good it's scary. Bennett doesn't just look and sound like Garland; she becomes her, capturing the desperate vulnerability and manic energy of a woman fighting to hang onto her career and her sanity.
